936
00:49:22,630 --> 00:49:23,189
Scott: And searching for a channel.

937
00:49:23,831 --> 00:49:25,250
Rym: So, basically, eventually...

938
00:49:25,250 --> 00:49:28,570
Scott: But we have two people, so we actually need four antennas and two searching for channels.

939
00:49:28,650 --> 00:49:33,570
Rym: So, eventually, you get into, like, if you go to Sure, the ULX S&P series.

940
00:49:33,770 --> 00:49:34,570
Scott: Aren't they competitors?

941
00:49:35,511 --> 00:49:38,630
Rym: Yeah, I'm just, I know Sure, and they seem to be the ones I'm going to buy.

942
00:49:38,914 --> 00:49:39,168
Scott: Okay.

943
00:49:39,791 --> 00:49:47,150
Rym: I've used, like, other types before, but I've always used them in the sense of either someone else rented them and I just configured them.

944
00:49:47,651 --> 00:49:48,821
