952
00:50:18,094 --> 00:50:19,830
Rym: So, they take different voltages.

953
00:50:20,370 --> 00:50:24,590
Rym: So, I came down to the ULX S&P versions.

954
00:50:25,350 --> 00:50:27,970
Rym: The differences between them are almost negligible.

955
00:50:28,390 --> 00:50:30,110
Scott: Why do they even have two different versions?

956
00:50:30,250 --> 00:50:32,530
Rym: So, the S is considered the prosumer version.

957
00:50:32,690 --> 00:50:36,030
Rym: It's pretty much awesome, but it doesn't have group scan.

958
00:50:36,351 --> 00:50:37,850
Rym: ULXP has group scan.

959
00:50:38,010 --> 00:50:39,650
Scott: So, group scan is when you have more than one.

960
00:50:40,010 --> 00:50:48,290
Rym: Group scan says the unit will find a group, because every different wireless system has a set of channel groups.

961
00:50:48,490 --> 00:50:51,670
Rym: So, you pick a group, and then each microphone needs a channel within that group.

962
00:50:52,550 --> 00:50:59,629
Rym: So, the group scan will find the group near you that has the least interference and thus most available channels.

963
00:51:00,070 --> 00:51:02,209
Scott: And then it will give one channel to one guy and one channel to the other guy?

964
00:51:02,331 --> 00:51:03,049
Rym: Basically, yes.

965
00:51:03,331 --> 00:51:07,550
Rym: Without group scan, you have to just fucking guess at which group and then scan within the group.

966
00:51:08,631 --> 00:51:19,948
