00:59:45,467 --> 00:59:45,508
Scott: PP."

1134
00:59:46,430 --> 00:59:51,590
Scott: And don't use any battery, you know, plug thingy except the DC whatever number, right?

1135
00:59:52,095 --> 00:59:53,490
Scott: So, I tried to get those model numbers.

1136
00:59:53,730 --> 00:59:58,390
Rym: Yeah, once you go pro, very specific model numbers of things mean a lot to you.

1137
00:59:59,030 --> 01:00:05,870
Scott: So, I go and I finally B&H'd and miraculously they had the fake battery bit, but they didn't have an AC adapter.

1138
01:00:06,751 --> 01:00:10,147
Scott: How do they order a not equal number of both products?

1139
01:00:10,227 --> 01:00:10,770
Scott: I do not know.

1140
01:00:11,591 --> 01:00:13,930
Scott: So, I go searching on the internet for the AC adapter.

1141
01:00:15,071 --> 01:00:17,450
Scott: No one has it, except like some Japanese places.

1142
01:00:17,690 --> 01:00:20,248
Scott: And it's like, "Wow, are they just not selling this

1143
01:00:20,268 --> 01:00:20,429
Scott: here?".

1144
01:00:20,671 --> 01:00:20,935
Rym: Yeah.

1145
01:00:21,665 --> 01:00:21,989
Scott: Well, here.

1146
01:00:22,290 --> 01:00:27,509
Scott: But then I noticed the GH3 had the exact same batteries as the GH4.

1147
01:00:28,611 --> 01:00:35,109
Scott: It had the exact same DC coupling bit, but it had a different AC adapter, the AC8, not the AC10.

1148
01:00:35,550 --> 01:00:40,688
Scott: And I'm like, "Huh, why wouldn't the AC8 work in the same as the AC10

1149
01:00:40,969 --> 01:00:41,170
Scott: does?".

1150
01:00:41,390 --> 01:00:50,403
Scott: I mean, clearly they've changed the product, but this takes the same batteries as that camera and the same DC coupler and the same everything.

1151
01:00:50,463 --> 01:00:52,210
Scott: Why wouldn't it use the same, right?

1152
01:00:52,771 --> 01:00:55,309
Scott: So, I decided to take a risk for the internets.

1153
01:00:56,010 --> 01:01:01,290
Scott: I went and I bought the Wasabi batteries meant for the GH3, the third-party batteries, and I stuck them in there.

1154
01:01:01,450 --> 01:01:02,296
Scott: Camera could have exploded.

